name: Stupor Looper
description:
The Stupor Looper is a simple and sweet feedback looper. Coupled with your choice of pedals, it's an excellent way to get yourself into noise, glitch and good-times. Available in a variety of shapes and sizes, with a whole bunch of varied features. True bypass inside an 125b aluminium frame, painted however you want with options for horizontal or vertical switch placement, or soft touch momentary feedback looping, handwired by yours truly. Please choose your options before checkout!

Expect: overspray, reliability, near-indestructibility Do not expect: bad times, digital grossness, the end of times. Used by James from Mega Ogre, Chumpy from Polar Knights and Cull.

name: Xprss Urslf
description:
Sometimes, you buy the nicest pant suit and you just need to accessorise. There's something missing, something you need to add. It's time to xprss urslf.

So, Solwat provides the Xprss Urslf customisable external control pedal. Offering your choice tap tempo and expression pedal in one convenient 1590A case, the Xprss Urslf is suitable for all pedals with a pre-existing Expression/Control input.

Three combinations available - tap & tap, expression & tap, or expression and expression. Just include your preference in the order box, and have a great time, painted to your specifications.

name: Faux Train Pedal Board
description:
Pedalboards are expensive. Some would say too expensive - especially for us poor Australians, what with shipping and all. From your mate Solwat and his mate Ed comes a practical and personal solution to organise your sweet chain of pedals. 

Each board is made to order for your exact needs. Wood selection of your choice, stain of your choice as well. Please contact for more details and goodtimes.

Used by members of Cogel, Chance Waters and Cull.

name: iPatch
description:
Revolutionary. Exciting. Innovative. Beautiful.

The iPatch is none of these things, but is an excellent way to organise your pedalboard, centralising your in/outs and making your day the best day every time you get your board out. 

Want to screw around with your chain day in, day out, but worried about finding the end of your line? The iPatch will help. Got a small board and want to push it to the edge? The iPatch is your pedal.

Passive circuit inside an aluminium frame, painted however you want, handwired by yours truly.

Expect: overspray, reliability, near-indestructibility, lifetime warranty. 

Do not expect: bad times, digital grossness, the end of times.

name: Weightlifter
description:
Going to the gym is hard, especially when you're a musician. That's why some genius invented the A/B splitter so  that instead of weights, we can sit down and let something else do it for us. 

Seriously though, the Weightlifter is dual switch A/B/Y splitter that allows for post-chain amp selection or individual/simultaneous chain selection for all you pedal lovers who like playing with a complex chain and dry/wet combinations (alternatively, consider the Solwat 'Will It Blend?'.

Buffered for tone preservation inside a solid aluminium frame, painted however you want, handwired by yours truly.

Expect: overspray, reliability, near-indestructibility.

Do not expect: bad times, digital grossness, the end of times.

name: Will It Blend?
description:
Sometimes, you're going to be making a lot of noise. Maybe you bought a Stupor Looper from some sweetheart and you love it - but you still want to be able to hear your sweet, sweet melodious goodtimes over the top. 

That's when you ask Will It Blend? and pick up one of these pedals. Chances are it will blend and be totally fantastic.

Buffered for tone preservation with true bypass as an option, inside a solid aluminium frame, painted however you want, handwired by yours truly.

Expect: overspray, reliability, near-indestructibility.

Do not expect: bad times, digital grossness, the end of times
